ndex The Barthel Index for Activities of Daily Living is an ordinal scale which measures a </span></p><p class="pf0" style="text-align: center;"><span class="cf1">of Daily Living person's ability to complete activities of daily living (ADL). It measures the degree </span></p><p class="pf0"></p><p class="pf0" style="text-align: center;"><span class="cf1">Activities of assistance required by an individual on ten mobility and self-care ADL items. A </span></p><p class="pf0" style="text-align: center;"><span class="cf1">Personal Care  score out of 100 indicates the level of function with 100 representing independences </span></p><p class="pf0"></p><p class="pf0" style="text-align: center;"><span class="cf1">in all items. Full data is recorded in the Appendix. </span></p><p class="pf0" style="text-align: center;"><span class="cf1">MBI Score  100/100 </span></p><p class="pf0"></p><p class="pf0" style="text-align: center;"><span class="cf1">MBI Score meaning  â€¢ 0 â€“ 20: Total dependency (Very High Care Need).  </span></p><p class="pf0" style="text-align: center;"><span class="cf1">â€¢ 21 â€“ 60: Severe dependency (Very High Care Need). </span></p><p class="pf0" style="text-align: center;"><span class="cf1">â€¢ 61 â€“ 90: Moderate dependency (Moderate Care Need). </span></p><p class="pf0" style="text-align: center;"><span class="cf1">â€¢ 91 â€“ 99: Slight dependency (Minimal care need). </span></p><p class="pf0" style="text-align: center;"><span class="cf1">â€¢ 100: Independent. </span></p><p class="pf0"></p><p class="pf0" style="text-align: center;"><span class="cf1">Areas requiring â€¢ No assistance requires with personal care. </span></p><p class="pf0" style="text-align: center;"><span class="cf1">assistance </span></p><p class="pf0"></p><p class="pf0"><span class="cf1"> </span></p><p class="pf0"><span class="cf1"> </span></p><p class="pf0"><span class="cf1"> </span></p><p class="pf0"></p><p class="pf0" style="text-align: center;"><span class="cf1">Lawtonâ€™s Scale Ac